    - rid: 5422255950001341321
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Hi! How are you?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341322
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Did you finished?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341323
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: 'You have to find <color=#03FCF0>Awakening herbs</color>, it should
          be in somewhere in forest. I need 8 plants to prepare awakening potion. '
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341324
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: You made it! Give potion to Kaelen and wake him up!
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341325
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Go to Kaelen and ask him about his dreams.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341326
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: You already killed forest demon? Great!
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341327
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Go to the south, there is demon in forest who has poisoned many trees.
          He also can be responsible for people who can't wake up. Do what you have
          to do.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341328
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: 'He was locked in his sleep. '
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341329
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: To find out exactly what was going on there, it would be best to fall
          asleep myself, but I can't do that.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341330
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: But you, you have a patron, right? Maybe you could try?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341331
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Come back in the next patch. Then we'll try to lock you in a dream.
          And maybe the druid grove will be more... druidic.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341332
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Of course, I came to town to solve this mystery.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341333
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Great! To find a way to lock you in your sleep, I need a way... Hmmm...
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 5422255950001341334
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Come back in the next patch. I should have found a way by then.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
